cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories, as it deals with the robustness of deep neural networks against adversarial attacks. The use of one-shot neural architecture search also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The study of network architectures and their resilience to attacks falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the use of finetuning and the exploration of flow of solution procedure (FSP) matrix suggest a focus on neural networks (cs.NE).
